McClory also denied a further charge of assaulting a police officer but pleaded guilty to the criminal damage of a police custody blanket when she was detained.

Blair Martin, prosecuting, told the court: 'A barman at the Wetherspoons was aware of some activity in the female toilets in the upstairs part of the bar.

'He goes upstairs to hear noises coming from one of the cubicles.

'Police attended because they would not come out and police had to force entry into the cubicle.

